{"parse":{"title":"Andrew Harper's Hideaway Report","pageid":22680710,"revid":796967769,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Update\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"Ambox current red.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Ambox_current_red.svg/42px-Ambox_current_red.svg.png\" width=\"42\" height=\"34\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Ambox_current_red.svg/63px-Ambox_current_red.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Ambox_current_red.svg/84px-Ambox_current_red.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"360\" data-file-height=\"290\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article needs to be <b>updated</b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please update this article to reflect recent events or newly available information.</span>  <small><i>(July 2014)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Andrew Harper's Hideaway Report</b></i> is a monthly <a href=\"/wiki/Newsletter\" title=\"Newsletter\">newsletter</a> that reviews <a href=\"/wiki/Luxury_hotel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Luxury hotel\">luxury hotels</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Resort\" title=\"Resort\">resorts</a>, typically smaller, more individual ventures.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The first issue appeared in 1979.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \"Andrew Harper,\" a <a href=\"/wiki/Pseudonym\" title=\"Pseudonym\">pseudonym</a>, was concerned about the influence of commercial considerations on <a href=\"/wiki/Travel\" title=\"Travel\">travel</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Review\" title=\"Review\">reviews</a>, so he travels anonymously and pays his own expenses.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Each year, the company conducts a <a href=\"/wiki/Opinion_poll\" title=\"Opinion poll\">survey</a> of subscribers' favorite small hotels.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Andrew Harper, LLC employs 80 full-time staff with offices in <a href=\"/wiki/Austin,_Texas\" title=\"Austin, Texas\">Austin</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Chicago\" title=\"Chicago\">Chicago</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City\" title=\"New York City\">New York</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (August 2015)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> It also operates a luxury <a href=\"/wiki/Travel_agency\" title=\"Travel agency\">travel agency</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Harper%27s_Hideaway_Report&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/andrew-harper/perfect-hideaways-with-10_b_3348656.html\">\"Ten Perfect Small Hideaways\"</a>. <i>The Huffington Post</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">August 6,</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Huffington+Post&amp;rft.atitle=Ten+Perfect+Small+Hideaways&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.com%2Fandrew-harper%2Fperfect-hideaways-with-10_b_3348656.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrew+Harper%27s+Hideaway+Report\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Andrew Harper. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thedailybeast.com/galleries/2013/09/07/top-20-international-small-hotels-andrew-harper-s-picks-photos.html\">\"Top 20 International Small Hotels: Andrew Harper's Picks (Photos)\"</a>. <i>The Daily Beast</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">August 6,</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Daily+Beast&amp;rft.atitle=Top+20+International+Small+Hotels%3A+Andrew+Harper%27s+Picks+%28Photos%29&amp;rft.au=Andrew+Harper&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailybeast.com%2Fgalleries%2F2013%2F09%2F07%2Ftop-20-international-small-hotels-andrew-harper-s-picks-photos.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrew+Harper%27s+Hideaway+Report\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.forbes.com/forbes-life-magazine/2004/0914/108.html\">\"Checking In, Sir?\"</a>. <i>Forbes</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">August 6,</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Forbes&amp;rft.atitle=Checking+In%2C+Sir%3F&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%